      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:29:7",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ لَبِسَ السَّرَاوِيلَ مِنْ قُعُودٍ وُقِيَ وَجَعَ الْخَاصِرَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from one of his companions, from Muhammad Bin Khalid Al Tayalisy, from Ali Bin Abu Hamza, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who wears trousers whilst seated would not get groin pain’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "7. Abu Ali al-Ash‘ariy has narrated from certain persons of his people from Muhammad ibn Khalid al-Tayalisy from Ali ibn abu Hamzah from abu Basir who have said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘If one wears a loincloth in a sitting position, he remains safe from lower back pain.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
